006-Sensitivity Analysis of One Paramter

Central Limit Theorem

2019-05-14

1 Introduction

Often in statistics, we are required to perform sensitivity analyses to see the effect of parameters on inference. Here I provide a simple illustration of performing such a task in an efficient and reproducible way using the function (Xie 2015, 2013, 2014). We use the demonstration of the Central Limit Theorem (CLT) in action (Joseph 2010) as an example.
